Wow, 46 posts in the discussion in the first ten hours of it being posted. I doubt that's a record, but it is certainly a lot.

Anyway, to address some of the issues brought up (in no particular order):

Though I find the idea of it being in the asteroid belt or around Jupiter intriguing, I find that takes away from some of the creepiness. I also have to ask myself how in the world (puntastic!) we would have ever discovered it.

I understand some people's issue that this SCP appears somewhat "uncontained." However, to explain my logic, this SCP is being contained by observing it, which the Foundation is doing. It currently isn't doing much besides transmitting, which the Foundation is working on stopping. The Foundation does have the option of attempting to destroy it (I originally included a blurb about using a rail gun, but decided it was out of place), but destroying it may in fact cause more trouble than leaving it alone. Read up like 6 posts; Sorts has a good explanation as to why destroying it would be a bad idea.

As far as blocking or changing the data it gathers, I also considered this, but I feel as though that requires a better understanding of the SCP than is appropriate to maintain creepiness.

EDIT: Haha, I almost forgot to answer the question directly above this post. Anyway, as to space junk, I do have a plan for that, but it ties in with the [DATA EXPUNGED] in the test log, so I won't go into detail.

I hope this clears up some issues, or at least explains my logic behind them. Thanks for all the feedback guys, I really appreciate it!





